00:11:29,313 --> 00:11:31,565
But if I'm helping you guys, I say,

240
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:34,318
"What has one thumb
and wants to keep going?

241
00:11:34,402 --> 00:11:35,778
This not-lady."

242
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:38,739
Eh? Eh?

243
00:11:40,741 --> 00:11:43,953
Okay, so that was trolley problem
version number seven.

244
00:11:44,036 --> 00:11:47,081
Chidi opted to run over
five William Shakespeares

245
00:11:47,164 --> 00:11:50,376
instead of one Santa Claus.

246
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:53,462
As much as I'm enjoying
watching random people's heads fly off,

247
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:56,590
I think we've taken this trolley thing
as far as it can go.

248
00:11:56,674 --> 00:11:59,593
-You might be right, Eleanor.
-Thank you.

249
00:11:59,677 --> 00:12:01,554
Let's try the doctor one.

250
00:12:02,721 --> 00:12:04,056
Dude! What the fork?

251
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:07,643
[Michael] These five people all need
organ transplants or they will die.

252
00:12:07,726 --> 00:12:09,061
Eleanor's perfectly healthy.

253
00:12:09,145 --> 00:12:10,855
Chidi, do you want to slice her open

254
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:13,023
and use her organs
to save the five sick people?

255
00:12:13,107 --> 00:12:14,608
Chidi, think about this.

256
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:17,153
I'm your hottest friend. No, Tahani.

257
00:12:17,236 --> 00:12:18,988
I'm your nicest... No, Jason.

258
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,406
I'm your friend!

259
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:22,074
[Chidi] I won't do it.

260
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:24,827
As a doctor, I've taken
the Hippocratic oath to do no harm.

261
00:12:24,910 --> 00:12:26,370
Although five people will die,

262
00:12:26,454 --> 00:12:30,082
I cannot harm one innocent person
to save them and forsake my oath.

263
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,167
It's unethical.

264
00:12:32,626 --> 00:12:34,962
-Okay, tell their families.
-What?

265
00:12:38,966 --> 00:12:40,050
[girl] Doctor Chidi?

266
00:12:40,676 --> 00:12:44,597
My daddy needed a heart transplant.
Did you save his life?

267
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:46,265
He was working,

268
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:49,518
then a really bad man
ran him over with a trolley.

269
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,937
Oh! Come on!

270
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:55,065
What? I'm finding this incredibly helpful.

271
00:12:55,149 --> 00:12:57,109
I'm really starting to get it.

272
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,027
I know!

273
00:12:58,110 --> 00:13:00,905
We'll do the one where you're in a boat
next to a volcano

274
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:05,326
and you can either save 50 people
or one awesome dog or whatever.

275
00:13:05,409 --> 00:13:06,535
No, no, no.

276
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:08,829
Hey! Are you torturing us again?

277
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:10,831
What?

278
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:12,625
You don't care
about learning ethics lessons.

279
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:14,835
You're just torturing Chidi again,
aren't you?

280
00:13:16,504 --> 00:13:17,671
-Busted.
-What?

281
00:13:17,755 --> 00:13:19,340
[laughs maniacally]

282
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:21,717
I'm sorry.

283
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,969
Old habits die hard.

284
00:13:24,053 --> 00:13:26,680
Not as hard as those people
you crushed with the trolley, though.

285
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:29,058
-Boom!
-I'm sorry, is this funny to you?

286
00:13:29,141 --> 00:13:31,393
Yeah. I thought that was clear
from my laughter.

287
00:13:32,144 --> 00:13:33,437
Oh, come on.

288
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:35,064
My bad.

289
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:37,733
I'm still on your team, okay?

290
00:13:37,816 --> 00:13:40,569
I just needed to let off
a little steam. [grunts]

291
00:13:41,570 --> 00:13:43,322
See? Back home, all good.

292
00:13:43,405 --> 00:13:45,950
No. No, not all good.

293
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:49,537
You keep saying we need you
or we'll end up getting tortured forever.

294
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:53,457
But then, when we do help you out,
we still end up getting tortured.

295
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:57,628
I'd rather just be tortured
than choose it.

296
00:13:57,711 --> 00:13:59,505
You are no longer welcome in my class.

297
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,465
Get the fork out!

298
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:08,973
But I said, "My bad."

299
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:10,349
Out!

300
00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,060
[Eleanor] You okay?

301
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:15,938
You've been staring at the second page
of this book for an hour.

302
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,982
When I'm really upset,

303
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:21,610
concentrating on a table of contents
helps me calm down.

304
00:14:21,694 --> 00:14:25,823
It's like a menu, but the food is words.

305
00:14:25,906 --> 00:14:27,324
Oh. Okay.

306
00:14:27,408 --> 00:14:30,536
I can't believe I actually thought
he wanted to learn from us.

307
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:32,371
What he really wanted was to torture me.

308
00:14:32,454 --> 00:14:34,415
Using the thing I love most in the world.

309
00:14:34,498 --> 00:14:35,374
Woven belts?

310
00:14:36,208 --> 00:14:37,334
Oh! Teaching, right.

311
00:14:38,752 --> 00:14:40,379
I'm sorry about this, Chidi.

312
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:44,049
I made him take the classes
and I feel a little responsible.

313
00:14:44,133 --> 00:14:45,801
No, no, it's not your fault.

314
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:47,595
Yeah, you're right, it isn't,
and no takebacks.

315
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:49,471
No, a tiger can't change his stripes.

316
00:14:50,222 --> 00:14:51,932
This is what he always wanted.

317
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:55,936
Me trying desperately to teach him
something he never intended to learn

318
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:57,354
so I'd end up miserable

319
00:14:57,438 --> 00:15:00,941
with my glasses all smudged up
from sweaty forehead stress grease.

320
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:05,195
Okay. Gross.
Also, I really don't think that's true.

321
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:10,200
No? What possible other reason
could he have to behave that way?

322
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:13,495
Actually, I can think of one.

323
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:19,084
Yesterday, Tahani gave us her reasons
not to take this relationship public.

324
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:23,297
-Tahani, what do you value about Jason?
-Well, he's thoughtful.

325
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:25,716
Picks flowers and brings them to me.

326
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,510
Often, they're ones
I've just planted, but...

327
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:29,720
That's how I know they're fresh.

328
00:15:29,803 --> 00:15:32,890
He's the least self-aware person
I've ever met.

329
00:15:32,973 --> 00:15:35,684
He has massive amounts
of unearned confidence

330
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,979
and he's utterly unaware
of his own absurdity.

331
00:15:39,063 --> 00:15:41,148
Therefore, quite good at sex.

332
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:45,569
Here's the thing.
I'm nice to you and you're mean to me.

333
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:50,324
There's something wrong about that,
but I can't put my finger on what it is.

334
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:55,829
Jason, I genuinely like you
but it's hard to change all at once.

335
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:58,082
Can you give me a little more time?

336
00:15:58,666 --> 00:15:59,625
Okay.

337
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:03,003
I agree to keep this on the DL for now

338
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:06,131
if you agree to grab my butt in public
once a week.

339
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:10,219
You can say I sat in gum
and you're trying to scrape it off.

340
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:13,138
You do sit in a lot of gum.

341
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:16,517
[Janet] Aw. I'm happy for you guys.

342
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:19,311
[retches]

343
00:16:21,730 --> 00:16:22,731
[ribbits]

344
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,234
-[ribbits]
-Huh.

345
00:16:25,317 --> 00:16:29,947
Look, I don't know what to tell you.
If Chidi can't take a joke, that's on him.

346
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:33,075
Just like all that blood was.
[chuckles]

347
00:16:33,158 --> 00:16:34,618
I can't high-five that!

348
00:16:35,327 --> 00:16:37,121
No matter how badly I want to.

349
00:16:37,204 --> 00:16:40,749
Look, this isn't about Chidi
not being able to take a joke.

350
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:41,959
This is about you.

351
00:16:42,042 --> 00:16:46,005
You're doing what I used to do.
You're pulling an Eleanor.

352
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:50,426
Posting my cousin's credit card number
on Reddit because she said I looked tired?

353
00:16:50,509 --> 00:16:52,428
[both chuckle]

354
00:16:52,511 --> 00:16:53,804
I forgot I did that.

355
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,265
No. No.

356
00:16:56,348 --> 00:17:00,352
Pulling an Eleanor in this case is
lashing out when you feel like a failure.

357
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,312
You couldn't hack the classes.

358
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:05,482
They made you feel dumb and small,
so you took it out on the teacher.

359
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,943
You think I feel dumb and small?

360
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:11,280
I'm an eternal being
who can see in nine dimensions.

361
00:17:11,363 --> 00:17:12,614
I can see from your aura

362
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:15,159
you're about to fart quietly
then lie about it.

363
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:18,037
And please don't,
because I can also see what you ate today.

364
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,456
Dude, you can bluster
and insult all you want.

365
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,708
Also classic Shellstrop moves, by the way.

366
00:17:22,791 --> 00:17:24,793
But deep down, you know I'm right.

367
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:25,836
Whatever.

368
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,047
Eventually Chidi will get over it.

369
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:31,884
[chuckles] Leaving it up to
the other person to be the grown-up.

370
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:34,470
Yet another classic Shellstrop move.

371
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:36,472
You and I are really very similar.

372
00:17:37,139 --> 00:17:38,515
What does that say about me?

373
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:43,270
Look, bro, it's 100% on you
to make this up to him.

374
00:17:47,191 --> 00:17:48,358
[Michael] <i>I screwed up.</i>

375
00:17:49,151 --> 00:17:52,738
I'm owning it.
I mean, I'm a superior being.

376
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:54,406
I ought to act like one. Right?

377
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:57,743
So, I really thought
about each one of you,

378
00:17:57,826 --> 00:18:00,370
and I got you something
that will make you happy.

379
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:03,624
I call them "opposite tortures."

380
00:18:03,707 --> 00:18:06,668
-Do you mean "presents"?
-That's better. Thank you.

381
00:18:06,752 --> 00:18:08,462
Tahani, here's yours.

382
00:18:10,214 --> 00:18:11,632
Holy mama!

383
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,134
Is this a diamond?

384
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:16,762
Yeah. Honestly, I don't get the appeal.

385
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:21,433
Diamonds are literally carbon molecules
lined up in the most boring way.

386
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:23,227
They're worthless space garbage.

387
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:26,480
What you're holding right now,
that's basically meteorite poop.

388
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,357
And I have the biggest piece!

389
00:18:28,440 --> 00:18:34,363
Eleanor, I had Janet make you
a never-ending shrimp dispensary.

390
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:36,698
[Eleanor gasps]

391
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,367
[Michael laughs]

392
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:41,370
[exclaims loudly]

393
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:44,414
This is the dream.

394
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:46,416
-It is?
-Yeah.

395
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,836
Jason, here you go.

396
00:18:49,837 --> 00:18:52,548
[gasps] Pikachu! Guys, it's Pikachu!

397
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:54,007
This is awesome.

398
00:18:56,176 --> 00:18:57,678
Aw, man.

399
00:18:58,303 --> 00:19:00,472
And, finally, Chidi.

400
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:04,059
You were a tough nut to crack,
but I think I figured it out.

401
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:12,985
This is a replica of a lost notebook
from the desk of Immanuel Kant.

402
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:18,740
It contains never-before-seen thoughts
and musings and several...

403
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:21,702
crude, erotic doodles.

404
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:23,162
Interesting guy, actually.

405
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:28,792
The point is no one on Earth
has ever seen this, except for you.

406
00:19:29,585 --> 00:19:30,586
Cool.

407
00:19:31,837 --> 00:19:35,674
This isn't an apology.
It's a bribe and I'm not interested.

408
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:37,259
Yeah, we can't be bought!

409
00:19:37,342 --> 00:19:38,635
What do you want from me, man?

410
00:19:38,719 --> 00:19:42,181
You want me to give you
a golden nameplate for your office?

411
00:19:42,264 --> 00:19:44,391
Or you want a diamond
bigger than Tahani's?

412
00:19:44,474 --> 00:19:47,227
No! Then this would be worthless.

413
00:19:47,311 --> 00:19:48,478
I don't want anything.

414
00:19:48,562 --> 00:19:51,815
Oh... Okay. I get it.

415
00:19:51,899 --> 00:19:54,318
I get it.
You want me to admit I was wrong.

416
00:19:54,401 --> 00:19:57,613
You want me to say, "Chidi, I'm so sorry,

417
00:19:57,696 --> 00:20:00,699
because I didn't understand human ethics
and you do.

418
00:20:00,782 --> 00:20:03,744
It made me feel insecure and I lashed out.

419
00:20:03,827 --> 00:20:08,540
And please help me, because I feel
so, so lost and vulnerable."

420
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:11,627
Yes.

421
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,425
Oh, Chidi, I'm so sorry.

422
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:22,346
I didn't understand human ethics
and you do.

423
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:26,308
And it made me feel insecure
and I lashed out.

424
00:20:27,643 --> 00:20:33,232
And I really need your help,
because I feel so lost and vulnerable.

425
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,485
Have a seat.

426
00:20:37,110 --> 00:20:38,070
[sniffles]

427
00:20:42,324 --> 00:20:43,242
Whoo!

428
00:20:43,992 --> 00:20:45,702
Nobody try "mystery flavor."

429
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:48,038
It's white chocolate and it is nasty.

430
00:20:51,458 --> 00:20:55,045
Listen, we just wanted to thank you
for all of your help.

431
00:20:55,128 --> 00:20:58,006
{\an8}Our relationship's grown so much stronger
over the past few weeks

432
00:20:58,090 --> 00:20:59,174
{\an8}and we owe it all to you.

433
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:02,844
{\an8}Congratulations.
I am very happy for the both of you.

434
00:21:02,928 --> 00:21:04,930
{\an8}[rumbling and crashing]

435
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:07,557
{\an8}Okay, bye!

436
00:21:15,399 --> 00:21:16,400
{\an8}Hi, there.

437
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:18,151
{\an8}What's happening? What's wrong?

438
00:21:18,235 --> 00:21:22,239
{\an8}I am wrong. I can't stop glitching.
I don't know why and it's getting worse.

439
00:21:22,322 --> 00:21:26,285
{\an8}I fear this neighborhood
is in danger of total collapse.

440
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,204
So that's the main thing. How are you?
